-- Romanian Utility Courts Bids for Water-Treatment Plants
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2013-03-18T13:47:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/romanian-utility-courts-bids-for-water-treatment-plants.html
Apaserv Satu Mare SA, a Romanian
utility, is seeking bids to upgrade two water-treatment plants
and build a new one for about 22 million lei ($6.4 million).  Apaserv plans northern Romania plant improvements in
Negresti-Oas and Tasnad and to construct a new facility in
Livada, according to  a procurement notice  published today. Bids
can be submitted by May 14. The project is partly financed
through European Union funds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  